Package Lab3

Class EmployeeSet

java.lang.Object
Lab3.EmployeeSet
public class EmployeeSet extends Object
An Employee set is an array of Employee objects The same employee may not appear multiple times in a set. This bag was developed from the IntArrayBag class. Credit to Michael Main

  • Constructor Details

    • EmployeeSet

      public EmployeeSet()
      Initialize an empty set with an initial capacity of 10. Note that the add method works efficiently (without needing more memory) until this capacity is reached.

  • Method Details

    • size

      public int size()
      Accessor method to get the number of employees in this set.
      Returns:
      the number of employees in this set

    • capacity

      public int capacity()
      Accessor method to get the current capacity of this set. The add method works efficiently (without needing more memory) until this capacity is reached.
      Returns:
      the current capacity of this set

    • add

      public void add(Employee a)
      Add a new employee to this set. If the new employee would take this beyond its current capacity, then the capacity is increased before adding the new employee.
      Parameters:
      a - The new employee being added

    • remove

      public boolean remove(int eid)
      Remove one employee from the set
      Parameters:
      eid - the employee to remove from the set
      Returns:
      If the target was found in the set, then on copy of target was removed and the method returns true. Otherwise the set remains unchanged and the method returns false

    • contains

      public boolean contains(int eid)
      Accessor method to see if an employee is in the data set
      Parameters:
      eid - the id of the employee being searched for
      Returns:
      if the employee is found: true if the employee is not found: false
